title: Liberty's Cailey Sanchez gets best of childhood soccer coach
text:

Liberty girls soccer senior co-captain Cailey Sanchez found the top left corner of the net on a nice bending shot from about 25 yards out to clinch the Hurricanes' 3-2 win over rival Freedom on Thursday night. 
It was the second straight time Sanchez put in the game-winner against Freedom as she scored in overtime of last season's final meeting between the teams. 
The rivalry has even more meaning for Sanchez as she is competing against Freedom coach Bob Eaton, someone she is very familiar with. 
"I know the coach really well. He used to coach me growing up," Sanchez said. "So he's like, 'you did it to us again.'" 
The midfielder also assisted Taysia Snead for the first goal of the game with 36:03 left in the first half. 
"Sanchez does a hell of a job for us all the time," Liberty coach Scott Rodenbach said. 
Sanchez says she played for Eaton until she was 11 years old and owes a lot of her soccer skills to him. 
"He taught me everything I know," Sanchez said. "So he knows my strengths and weaknesses. But it's still a friendly competition so it's fun."
